descript.abstract: Humboldt County Highways and Roads, February 2019. This GIS dataset is the result of ongoing efforts to produce an accurate Roadway Centerline GIS layer for Humboldt County. Multiple source datasets were merged and edited to create this master roads layer. This centerline data consists of all public and some private roads in Humboldt County. Location geometry is based on 2005 Airphotos - USDA NAIP County Mosaic. Address ranges, City and Zip attributes have been checked and corrected using various sources including parcel site addresses. Roadway Functional Class is based on Humboldt County Travel Demand Forecasting Model.
descript.purpose: To be used as a general guide to Highways and Roads for Humboldt County for street and address location.

qhorizpa.horizpae: Please note the accuracy of GIS map data varies from location to location in the County. This GIS system is useful for planning purposes but should not be relied upon to determine property, zoning or general plan designation boundaries or be used in any way for project design. All GIS data should be verified before it is materially relied upon for property or project planning. In urban areas the GIS map data maybe inaccurate by as much as 50 feet in any direction. In rural areas the map data may be inaccurate by as much as 400 feet in any direction. This is a general accuracy disclaimer. Data may be more or less accurate depending on source informaton and digitizing methods.

citeinfo.title: Humboldt County Travel Demand Forecasting Model
USGS DLG
citeinfo.othercit:
The roads coverage was created with the USGS large scale (1:24,000) dlg's, along with roads from Shasta-Trinity, Six Rivers, Mendocino, Klamath, Rogue River, Siskiyou, Winema, and Umpqua National Forests, and California Department of Forestry (CDF) 1:24,000 roads as of October 1999. CDF roads were not consistent with the other datasets. Some of the 1:24,000 USGS roads data were obtained from Dr. Jim Strittholt (Earth Design Consultants, Corvalis Oregon). In spite of all these data sources, there were areas in the Rogue River Valley, Oregon and some of the California redwood region where USGS data was unavailable at the time of compilation. These areas represent gaps in the database.
Accuracy: 1:100,000 to 1:24,000

citeinfo.title: Humboldt County's 911 Contract Roads Centerline Dataset
citeinfo.othercit: This dataset was produced by LOGISYS for use in the Humboldt County Sherrif's 911 system. Ground checking of road names and address ranges was done by the sheriff 2000-2001 with check plots sent to the consultant. This dataset has fairly good attribution but is spatially inaccurate except in corrected areas. Filename: shapegeo

citeinfo.title: Modified Tiger File Roadway Centerline
citeinfo.othercit: : Numerous updates and corrections made to linework using scanned and rectified USGS 7.5' Quads (1995-1998). Attribute updating and checks were done using multiple sources. Most recent update (April 2001) used USGS 3.75' Digital Orthophoto Quarter Quads to correct linework for selected roads. For some areas, linework was corrected based on feedback from Local Fire Departments. Linework was corrected to match USGS DOQQ's - 2004 & 2005.

citeinfo.title: Humboldt County County GIS Parcel Data
citeinfo.othercit:
Humboldt County's Parcel Layer Vers. 2.5. This dataset is the result of an ongoing effort to produce an accurate county wide parcel layer. Digitizing began as far back as 1996. Includes all unincorporated areas as well as cities/incorporated areas. Cities data obtained from Arcata, Eureka, and Trinidad. Please note the accuracy of GIS map data varies from location to location in the County. This GIS system is useful for planning purposes but should not be relied upon to determine property, zoning or general plan designation boundaries or be used in any way for project design. All GIS data should be verified before it is materially relied upon for property or project planning.
Land Information System (LIS) database was joined to parcels to show Site Addresses for parcels for street name and address range corrections.
